'''Kevin José Rodríguez Cortez''' (born 4 March 2000) is an Ecuadorian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[Royale Union Saint-Gilloise]] and the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]].<ref>{{Soccerway}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Imbabura===
Born in [[Ibarra, Ecuador|Ibarra]], Rodríguez joined hometown side [[Imbabura S.C.|Imbabura]] at the age of 13. He progressed through the youth setup until making his first team debut in 2017, featuring in two matches as his club was relegated from the [[Ecuadorian Serie B|Serie B]].

Rodríguez started to feature more regularly in 2018, scoring seven times in the national stage of the [[Ecuadorian Segunda Categoria|Segunda Categoria]]. After scoring 11 goals overall during the 2019 season, he only scored once in five matches in 2020. In 2021, he only scored twice as his side returned to the second level.

Rodríguez became a regular starter for Imbabura in the [[2022 Ecuadorian Serie B|2022 Serie B]], scoring ten times as his side finished fifth.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://elnorte.ec/kevin-rodriguez-el-maximo-arponero-gardenio/|title=Kevin Rodríguez, el máximo arponero gardenio|trans-title=Kevin Rodríguez, the top scorer ''gardenio''|publisher=Diario El Norte|language=es|date=16 June 2022|accessdate=3 December 2022}}</ref> In the [[2022 Copa Ecuador]], he notably scored the winner to knock out [[L.D.U. Quito|LDU Quito]] in the round of 16.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lanacion.com.ec/kevin-rodriguez-luego-de-eliminar-a-ldu-estoy-concentrado-en-que-quiero-comerme-al-mundo/|title=Kevin Rodríguez luego de eliminar a LDU: "Estoy concentrado en que quiero comerme al mundo"|trans-title=Kevin Rodríguez right after knocking out LDU: "I am focused on taking on the world"|publisher=La Nación|language=es|date=22 July 2022|accessdate=3 December 2022}}</ref>

===Independiente del Valle===
On 2 December 2022, [[C.S.D. Independiente del Valle|Independiente del Valle]] announced the signing of Rodríguez.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://studiofutbol.com.ec/2022/12/02/oficial-kevin-rodriguez-nuevo-refuerzo-de-idv/|title=OFICIAL: Kevin Rodríguez, nuevo refuerzo de IDV|trans-title=OFFICIAL: Kevin Rodríguez, new addition of ''IDV''|publisher=Studio Fútbol|language=es|date=2 December 2022|accessdate=3 December 2022}}</ref>

===Union Saint-Gilloise===
On 1 September 2023, [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[Royale Union Saint-Gilloise|Union Saint-Gilloise]] announced the signing of Rodríguez on a four-year deal, with an option for an additional year.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Union secures striker Kevin Rodriguez |url=https://rusg.brussels/en/news/union-secures-striker-kevin-rodriguez |access-date=2023-09-01 |website=RUSG |language=en}}</ref> Rodríguez made his debut as a substitute in Union's opening [[2023-24 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]] group game against [[Toulouse F.C.|Toulouse]] on 21 September 2023, which Union drew 1–1.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2039194--union-sg-vs-toulouse/ |title=Union SG 1–1 Toulouse |publisher=UEFA |date=21 September 2023 }}</ref> Later that year, on 12 November, he scored his first goals by netting a brace in a 3–0 win over [[K.V. Kortrijk|Kortrijk]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/674500/kv-kortrijk-union-st-gilloise |title=Union St.-Gilloise 3–0 KV Kortrijk |publisher=ESPN |date=12 November 2023 }}</ref>

==International career==
Rodríguez was called up to the [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador national team]] for the first time in November 2022, as part of a preparation match against [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] ahead of the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] later that month.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://elnorte.ec/kevin-rodriguez-imbabura-sc-convocado-tricolor/ |title=Kevin Rodríguez, del Imbabura SC, convocado para amistoso con la Tricolor |trans-title=Kevin Rodríguez, from Imbabura SC, called up for a friendly with the Tricolor |work=Diario El Norte |date=5 November 2022 |access-date=14 November 2022 |language=es}}</ref> He made his debut in the match, which finished as a 0–0 draw, coming on as a substitute in the 63rd minute for [[José Cifuentes]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.elcomercio.com/deportes/mundial-catar/kevin-rodriguez-seleccion-ecuador-imbabura.html |title=Kevin Rodríguez, jugador del Imbabura, debutó en la Selección de Ecuador |trans-title=Kevin Rodríguez, Imbabura player, debuted in the Ecuador National Team |work=[[El Comercio (Ecuador)|El Comercio]] |date=12 November 2022 |access-date=14 November 2022 |language=es}}</ref> Two days later, he was included by coach [[Gustavo Alfaro]] in [[2022 FIFA World Cup squads#Ecuador|Ecuador's squad for the World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/futbol/quien-es-kevin-rodriguez-el-delantero-sorpresa-en-la-nomina-de-ecuador-para-qatar-2022-nota/ |title=¿Quién es Kevin Rodríguez? El delantero sorpresa en la nómina de Ecuador para Qatar 2022 |trans-title=Who is Kevin Rodríguez? The surprise striker in Ecuador's squad for Qatar 2022 |work=[[El Universo]] |date=14 November 2022 |access-date=14 November 2022 |language=es}}</ref>

On 12 October 2023, Rodríguez scored his first international goal – a 96th minute winner against [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]] in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification|qualifier]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com.ar/futbol/mundial/nota/_/id/12720340/kevin-rodriguez-fue-el-autor-del-gol-y-de-la-victoria-de-la-tri-sobre-bolivia|title=De criticado a héroe: Kevin Rodríguez fue el autor del gol y de la victoria de la Tri sobre Bolivia|language=Spanish|date=12 October 2023|access-date=11 November 2023|website=ESPN}}</ref>

Rodríguez was named in the Ecuadorian squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite tweet |author=Ecuador national football team |author-link=Ecuador national football team |user=LaTri |number=1592288685797494784 |date=14 November 2022 |title=Aquí están los 26 jugadores elegidos por el DT Gustavo Alfaro para jugar la Copa Mundial FIFA, estamos listos para hacer historia |trans-title=Here are the 26 players chosen by head coach Gustavo Alfaro to play the FIFA World Cup, we are ready to make history. |language=es |access-date=14 November 2022}}</ref> He was called up to the final 26-man Ecuador squad for the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eluniverso.com/deportes/futbol/ecuador-presenta-lista-oficial-para-la-copa-america-gonzalo-plata-y-robert-arboleda-quedaron-relegados-nota/|title=Ecuador presenta lista oficial para la Copa América: Gonzalo Plata y Robert Arboleda quedaron relegados|trans-title=Ecuador presents official roster for Copa America: Gonzalo Plata and Robert Arboleda left off the list|publisher=[[El Universo]]|date=29 May 2024|language=es}}</ref>

